title: US shoots down armed Turkish drone over Syria, Pentagon says
description: The United States has shot down an armed Turkish drone operating near its troops in Syria, the Pentagon said.

title: Watch as fire engulfs stand at Italian golf club where Ryder Cup was held last weekend
description: Firefighters in Italy have brought a fire under control in the grandstand of the golf club that hosted the Ryder Cup last weekend.

title: Hand grenade fragments found in bodies of victims after Prigozhin plane crash - Putin
description: Hand grenade fragments were found in the bodies of victims of a plane crash that killed former Wagner boss Yevgeny Prigozhin, Russian President Vladimir Putin has said.

title: September's temperature data was 'unprecedented' - and researchers are baffled at why extremes are so high
description: From climate scientists, the September temperature data has prompted a string of superlatives: "gobsmackingly bananas", "unprecedented", "staggering," "unnerving".

title: Boy, 6, among at least 51 dead in 'brutal' Russian rocket attack on cafe and shop, Ukraine says
description: At least 51 people, including a six-year-old boy, have died after a Russian rocket hit a village cafe and shop in eastern Ukraine in what the country's President Volodymyr Zelenskyy said was one of the deadliest attacks in months.

title: What was the Amritsar massacre - the event that led a man to try to kill the Queen?
description: Jaswant Singh Chail, who attempted to assassinate the late Queen Elizabeth II with a crossbow on Christmas Day in 2021, has been sentenced for treason at the Old Bailey.

title: 'An empire built on lies': Sam Bankman-Fried stole over $10bn from FTX customers, jury told
description: The trial of embattled crypto executive Sam Bankman-Fried has begun - with prosecutors claiming he stole more than $10bn (£8.2bn) from unsuspecting customers.

title: Thousands evacuated in Tenerife as summer wildfire re-ignites on holiday island
description: Authorities in Tenerife have evacuated around 3,000 people from their homes overnight as a wildfire sparked by high temperatures and strong winds raged in a forest already ravaged by fire in August.

title: Drivers in Singapore now need to pay £88,000 for permission to own a car (vehicle not included)
description: Drivers in Singapore now need to pay £88,000 for the right to own a car - and that doesn't include the cost of the vehicle itself.

title: Cricket World Cup: New Zealand vs England latest updates
India floods leave 14 dead and 100 missing after sudden rainfall swamps several towns
description: At least 14 people have died and more than 100 are missing after sudden rain flooded towns in northeastern India.

title: Biden's dog removed from White House after biting secret agents
description: Joe Biden's dog Commander has been removed from the White House after biting agents and staff.
